===Translations===
The following are publications that are claimed to be &quot;translations&quot; but have not been verified in scientific literature. According to Oleg Tvorogov and Igor Danilevsky, the unsystematic and arbitrary nature of the language of the Book of Veles makes it impossible to translate this work.

* Alexander Asov (B. Kresen)&#x27;s translation of the “Book of Veles” was published in 19 different editions, including:
** Russian Vedas. Songs of the bird Gamayun. Book of Veles / Restoration, translation, comments by B. Kresen (A. Asov) - Moscow: &quot;Science and Religion&quot;, 1992. - P. 133-273.
** Book of Veles. — Moscow: &quot;Manager&quot;, 1994. — 318 p. (This edition contains the original text with discrepancies; the volume of the book has been doubled compared to the 1992 edition based on new archival materials).
** Holy Russian Vedas. Book of Veles / Translation, explanations by A. Asov. - 3rd ed., Rev. and additional — Moscow: &quot;FAIR&quot;, 2007. — 576 p. - ISBN 978-5-8183-1277-4.

